column5: I normally don't have a heavy breakfast during the week, but today I decided to make an exception and do a lil fry up....  Good old western sandwich with homemade hash browns....
I have a feeling you'll be skipping lunch
Is that quishe?   Got the pot roast in the crock pot now waiting for me to wake up from my nap.

It's a western Omlette (green peeper, onions, ham, 3 eggs and cheddar cheese) with homemade hash browns...  BillM....I shared some with my wife   .....and you're right....I'm good now until dinner after I get back from doin some   out on the river
lets hope you egt a big walleye!  great brakefast steve....... but for me its DINNER TIME !
I could get into one of them omelets about now. Yummy.
I know Musky season is still a couple of months away but I'm looking forward to lunch at the Log Cabin come when we take a break on opening day
Taking a break and going in for lunch on OPENING DAY FOR MUSKIE   ?????  Paul,  The only break I'll be taking that day is when I open up my ziplock bag to grab a sandwich in the BOAT
yyyyyyuummm.  Nothing like a hardy breaky to keep that blood flowing beneath the wading belt.  Did you caramelize dem onions first?  cheers HD
